<div class="step-explanation">This mark is for finding the distance of the first part of the journey. You needed to calculate $\frac{1}{10} \times 200 = 20$ miles.</div>

<div class="step-title">Step 2: Method Mark <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span></div>
<div class="step-explanation">This mark is for calculating the time taken for the first part of the journey. Since you know the distance is 20 miles and the speed limit is 40 mph, you can calculate the time using the formula: Time = Distance / Speed. So, $\frac{20}{40} = 0.5$ hours, or 30 minutes. The <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span> can be awarded if you have $\frac{1}{10} \times \frac{200}{40} \times 60$ or if you simply state 0.5 hours or 30 minutes.</div>

<div class="step-title">Step 3: Method Mark <span class="marking-code">[M1]</span></div>
<div class="step-explanation">Similar to Step 1, this mark is for finding the distance of the second part of the journey. You needed to calculate $0.4 \times 200 = 80$ miles.</div>

<div class="step-title">Step 4: Method Mark <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span></div>
<div class="step-explanation">This mark is for calculating the time taken for the second part of the journey. The distance is 80 miles and the speed limit is 50 mph. So, the time is $\frac{80}{50} = 1.6$ hours, which is equal to 96 minutes. The <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span> can be awarded if you have $0.4 \times \frac{200}{50}$ or if you simply state 1.6 hours or 96 minutes. This mark is dependent on the previous <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span> mark.</div>

<div class="step-title">Step 5: Method Mark <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span></div>
<div class="step-explanation">This mark is for calculating the total time of the journey. You need to add the time for each part of the journey: 30 minutes + 96 minutes + 1 hour 30 minutes = 3 hours and 36 minutes. The <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span> is awarded for adding their previous calculated times together.</div>

<div class="step-title">Step 6: Accuracy Mark <span class="marking-code">[B5]</span></div>
<div class="step-explanation">This mark is for stating the correct arrival time. If Ryan leaves at 0850 and the journey takes 3 hours and 36 minutes, then the earliest arrival time is 1226 (12:26). If you have the correct working but state 12 26 am or 12 26 pm, you will still get the mark.</div>

<div class="step-title">Special Case 3 <span class="marking-code">[SC3]</span></div>
